.TH smi-versions-spider "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Packages Command"
.SH NAME
smi-versions-spider \- Crawl and identify versions of packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-versions-spider
.RI [ ARGUMENTS... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-versions-spider
is a utility that uses a Groovy helper script to crawl or identify package versions. It is typically used for maintaining version information within the SMI ecosystem.
